# Normalize line endings across Windows and Linux contributors.
# Authored 2026-05-23 by Jones (dIRT) to prevent the mode/CRLF noise that
# polluted the pre-split director-pattern repo.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` tells git: detect text files, store as LF, check out
# native on Windows. No more phantom "every line changed" diffs.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for files where line endings matter for execution.
*.py text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Binary — never touch these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.pdf binary
*.gz binary
*.zip binary
*.skill binary
